The paper deals with the correctness and fairness of Tendermint-core blockchains, which are distributed systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses consensus protocols and fault tolerance, which are common topics in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) categories. The paper also involves mathematical proofs and analysis, which are relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory) categories.
